Former United States child prodigy Freddy Adu will start a trial with AZ Alkmaar on Monday having been without a club since an unsuccessful spell with Brazilian side Bahia in 2013.

The 25-year-old attacker was a member of USA's 2008 Olympics team, but he has never fulfilled the potential that saw him burst on to the global scene when he signed for Major League Soccer side DC United at the age of 14 in 2004.

The Dutch club announced the trial on their website on Sunday, with a message saying they hoped the success of former AZ star and Adu's old USA Under-20 team-mate Jozy Altidore would inspire him to new heights.

